1
00:00:02,983 --> 00:00:04,949
-ONCE UPON A TIME...

2
00:00:04,949 --> 00:00:07,883
THERE WAS A MAN WHO DIED.

3
00:00:07,883 --> 00:00:11,516
THE MAN HAD THE POWER
TO MAKE STORIES COME TRUE.

4
00:00:11,516 --> 00:00:14,616
SO, HIS HANDS WERE CUT OFF
BY THE PEOPLE,

5
00:00:14,616 --> 00:00:18,849
WHO WERE AFRAID
OF TRAGEDIES BECOMING REALITY.

6
00:00:18,849 --> 00:00:23,483
WHEN THE MAN DIED, THE PEOPLE
HEAVED A GREAT SIGH OF RELIEF.

7
00:00:23,483 --> 00:00:27,483
AS IT TURNED OUT, HOWEVER,
WHEN HIS HANDS WERE CUT OFF,

8
00:00:27,483 --> 00:00:31,283
THE MAN HAD BEEN WRITING A STORY
IN HIS OWN BLOOD.

9
00:00:31,283 --> 00:00:34,649
THAT WAS A STORY
HE COULD CONTINUE SPINNING

10
00:00:34,649 --> 00:00:36,716
EVEN <i>AFTER</i> HE DIED --

11
00:00:36,716 --> 00:00:40,483
A STORY OF THE MAN HIMSELF.

12
00:00:40,483 --> 00:00:43,016
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

13
00:00:55,049 --> 00:00:58,083
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

14
00:01:22,883 --> 00:01:26,983
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

15
00:02:29,091 --> 00:02:30,925
-[ GASPS ]
[ COGS RATTLING ]

16
00:02:30,925 --> 00:02:32,358
[ GASPS ]

17
00:02:32,358 --> 00:02:34,725
WHAT?

18
00:02:34,725 --> 00:02:36,491
THIS CAN'T BE!

19
00:02:36,491 --> 00:02:40,458
TO THINK THE WORDS OF TRUE LOVE
TUTU WAS SUPPOSED TO SAY

20
00:02:40,458 --> 00:02:43,725
PRINCESS KRAEHE ENDED UP SAYING
INSTEAD.

21
00:02:43,725 --> 00:02:46,391
EVEN THOUGH SHE WAS RAISED
ON RAVEN'S BLOOD

22
00:02:46,391 --> 00:02:48,991
AND SHOULDN'T EVEN KNOW
HOW TO LOVE.

23
00:02:48,991 --> 00:02:50,825
[ LAUGHS ]

24
00:02:50,825 --> 00:02:54,191
REGARDLESS, YOU STILL WILL BE
UNABLE TO ESCAPE TRAGEDY,

25
00:02:54,191 --> 00:02:56,191
MY DEAR LITTLE DUCK.

26
00:02:56,191 --> 00:02:57,625
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

27
00:03:17,791 --> 00:03:20,691
-ARE -- ARE YOU GLAD TO HAVE IT,
PRINCE?

28
00:03:20,691 --> 00:03:22,625
-I DON'T KNOW.

29
00:03:22,625 --> 00:03:25,791
-SAY, UH...
I HAVE ANOTHER QUESTION.

30
00:03:25,791 --> 00:03:27,658
DO YOU THINK YOU'LL LOVE ME?

31
00:03:27,658 --> 00:03:29,125
-I DON'T KNOW.

32
00:03:30,625 --> 00:03:32,791
-WELL, JUST TELL ME YOU LOVE ME.

33
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:35,191
-I LOVE YOU.

34
00:03:35,191 --> 00:03:37,858
-I WANT TO HEAR YOU SAY
THAT YOU LOVE ME.

35
00:03:37,858 --> 00:03:40,958
TRUST ME, MYTHO, YOU DO LOVE.

36
00:03:40,958 --> 00:03:43,491
[ Crying ] PLEASE, I LOVE YOU!
MY PRINCE!

37
00:03:43,491 --> 00:03:48,491
I HAVE EVER SINCE I WAS LITTLE!
I'VE ALWAYS LOVED YOU!

38
00:03:48,491 --> 00:03:50,525
[ WIND HOWLING ]

39
00:03:53,758 --> 00:03:55,491
-RUE.

40
00:03:57,958 --> 00:03:59,925
-HE TOOK RUE.

41
00:03:59,925 --> 00:04:01,158
YOU MONSTER!

42
00:04:01,158 --> 00:04:04,391
-RELAX.
I HAVEN'T KILLED HER YET.

43
00:04:04,391 --> 00:04:06,125
SHE'S DEEP IN MY STOMACH.

44
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:09,158
I SHOULD'VE DONE THIS
IN THAT FIGHT LONG AGO

45
00:04:09,158 --> 00:04:11,358
AND SAVED US ALL THE TROUBLE.

46
00:04:11,358 --> 00:04:15,658
SHE'S JUST A HUMAN GIRL I
KIDNAPPED ON A WHIM AND RAISED,

47
00:04:15,658 --> 00:04:18,025
BUT SHE'S BEEN QUITE USEFUL.

48
00:04:18,025 --> 00:04:19,258
IF YOU KILL ME,

49
00:04:19,258 --> 00:04:21,891
YOU'LL BE KILLING
THE GIRL WITHIN ME, AS WELL.

50
00:04:21,891 --> 00:04:25,958
LIKEWISE, IF YOU SING ME AWAY.

51
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:28,991
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE BUT
TO OFFER UP YOUR HEART TO ME.

52
00:04:28,991 --> 00:04:32,058
-I CAN'T FIGHT, EVEN IF I RETURN
THE LAST HEART SHARD.

53
00:04:32,058 --> 00:04:33,358
HOW HORRIBLE!

54
00:04:33,358 --> 00:04:37,958
-PRINCE, I DEMAND YOU GIVE ME
YOUR HEART AT ONCE.

55
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:41,325
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

56
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:03,025
STILL RESISTING?

57
00:05:03,025 --> 00:05:08,258
YOU MEAN TO IMPLY YOU STILL HAVE
SOME CHANCE OF SUCCESS, PRINCE?

58
00:05:10,291 --> 00:05:12,925
-PRINCESS TUTU.
-YES?

59
00:05:12,925 --> 00:05:15,658
-I WOULD LIKE FOR YOU TO RETURN
MY FINAL HEART SHARD.

60
00:05:15,658 --> 00:05:16,658
-WHAT?

61
00:05:16,658 --> 00:05:18,025
-HMM.

62
00:05:18,025 --> 00:05:20,958
-PLEASE GIVE IT TO ME.
I HAVE TO SAVE HER.

63
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:26,758
NO, I-I WANT TO...SAVE RUE.

64
00:05:26,758 --> 00:05:28,458
EXCRUCIATING PAIN

65
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:32,825
OF HAVING RAVEN'S BLOOD EAT AT
YOUR HEART -- I KNOW THAT PAIN.

66
00:05:32,825 --> 00:05:35,258
IT STARTS IN THE WEAK PLACES
IN YOUR HEART

67
00:05:35,258 --> 00:05:36,591
AND SPREADS RUTHLESSLY.

68
00:05:36,591 --> 00:05:38,191
YOU CAN'T EVEN STOP YOURSELF

69
00:05:38,191 --> 00:05:40,991
FROM HURTING THE PEOPLE
WHO ARE IMPORTANT TO YOU.

70
00:05:43,225 --> 00:05:45,391
RUE HAS STOOD UP UNDER
THE BURDEN OF THAT SUFFERING

71
00:05:45,391 --> 00:05:48,391
ALL ALONE
EVER SINCE SHE WAS SMALL.

72
00:05:48,391 --> 00:05:53,891
HER LOVE WAS FRAIL, AND SHE WAS
ALWAYS AFRAID OF LOSING LOVE.

73
00:05:53,891 --> 00:05:56,191
THE MORE SHE LOVED,
THE MORE SHE SUFFERED,

74
00:05:56,191 --> 00:05:59,425
BUT THERE WAS NO ONE
SHE COULD EVEN SEEK HELP FROM.

75
00:05:59,425 --> 00:06:02,391
BUT SHE NEVER THOUGHT
TO STOP LOVING.

76
00:06:02,391 --> 00:06:07,391
WITH WORDS OF TRUE LOVE, SHE LED
ME OUT OF THE RAVEN'S DARKNESS.

77
00:06:07,391 --> 00:06:10,591
IT'S MY TURN TO PROTECT HER NOW,

78
00:06:10,591 --> 00:06:14,791
AND, IF POSSIBLE, I'D LIKE
TO TAKE RUE AS MY PRINCESS.

79
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:19,825
SO, PRINCESS TUTU...PLEASE
GIVE ME THE LAST HEART SHARD.

80
00:06:19,825 --> 00:06:21,391
-YES.

81
00:06:21,391 --> 00:06:24,258
[ CLASP CLICKS ]
-THANK YOU.

82
00:06:24,258 --> 00:06:26,558
-AH, YES.

83
00:06:26,558 --> 00:06:28,758
IF YOUR HEART IS NOT COMPLETE,

84
00:06:28,758 --> 00:06:31,491
I CANNOT GAIN ETERNAL LIFE
FROM IT.

85
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:35,725
I ALMOST RUSHED THINGS
IN MY EAGERNESS.

86
00:06:35,725 --> 00:06:36,791
-WHAT?

87
00:06:36,791 --> 00:06:38,925
[ WHIMPERS ]

88
00:06:38,925 --> 00:06:40,291
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

89
00:06:40,291 --> 00:06:42,725
-THE PENDANT WON'T COME OFF.

90
00:06:42,725 --> 00:06:45,158
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHY WON'T IT?

91
00:06:45,158 --> 00:06:47,125
-[ GROWLING ]

92
00:06:58,991 --> 00:07:00,858
-[ GASPS ]

93
00:07:00,858 --> 00:07:05,058
-PRINCESS TUTU,
I GRANT YOU UNTIL DAWN.

94
00:07:05,058 --> 00:07:09,391
YOU MUST GIVE THE FINAL SHARD
BACK TO THE PRINCE BY THEN.

95
00:07:09,391 --> 00:07:12,625
-AAAH!
-[ SHRIEKS ]

96
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:13,691
PRINCE!

97
00:07:13,691 --> 00:07:15,725
-IF YOU FAIL TO DO THIS,

98
00:07:15,725 --> 00:07:19,691
I WILL TEAR THE PRINCE'S HEART
INTO PIECES.

99
00:07:19,691 --> 00:07:21,525
-THIS TEA IS THE BLEND

100
00:07:21,525 --> 00:07:24,325
THAT DROSSELMEYER LIKED TO DRINK
WHILE HE WAS WORKING.

101
00:07:24,325 --> 00:07:28,458
HE USED THREE PARTS DARJEELING
AND THEN ADDED ASSAM.

102
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:30,125
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

103
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:31,191
[ HUFFS ]

104
00:07:31,191 --> 00:07:34,258
TELL ME AGAIN
WHY I MUST DO THIS.

105
00:07:34,258 --> 00:07:36,925
[ CAWING ]
IT CERTAINLY IS NOISY.

106
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:39,191
[ GASPS ]

107
00:07:39,191 --> 00:07:42,191
[ CAWING CONTINUES ]

108
00:07:42,191 --> 00:07:44,558
WH-WHAT'S GOING ON?!

109
00:07:44,558 --> 00:07:46,158
-WHAT?

110
00:07:46,158 --> 00:07:48,258
-BATHE IN HIS NOBLE BLOOD!

111
00:07:48,258 --> 00:07:51,058
ALL PEOPLE WILL BECOME CROWS!

112
00:07:51,058 --> 00:07:54,558
NOW CELEBRATE
MY TRIUMPHANT RETURN!

113
00:07:54,558 --> 00:07:56,925
-PIKE AND LILIE?

114
00:07:56,925 --> 00:07:58,458
[ CAWING CONTINUES ]

115
00:07:58,458 --> 00:07:59,825
MR. CAT?

116
00:07:59,825 --> 00:08:01,591
-YOU'D BETTER HURRY.

117
00:08:01,591 --> 00:08:04,825
YOU HAVEN'T MUCH TIME, TUTU.
-[ GASPS ]

118
00:08:04,825 --> 00:08:06,991
[ CRYING ]

119
00:08:06,991 --> 00:08:08,691
-HUH?

120
00:08:15,325 --> 00:08:18,991
[ SPARKLE! ]

121
00:08:18,991 --> 00:08:22,125
-[ STRAINING ]

122
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:23,425
[ PANTS ]

123
00:08:23,425 --> 00:08:26,025
I CAN'T TAKE IT OFF.
WHY NOT?!

124
00:08:26,025 --> 00:08:28,525
-I WONDER.
-[ GASPS ]

125
00:08:28,525 --> 00:08:30,391
-THIS IS BAD! FA--

126
00:08:30,391 --> 00:08:33,891
-AUTOR, I'M BEGGING YOU. WOULD
YOU PLEASE BE A LITTLE QUI--

127
00:08:33,891 --> 00:08:34,891
[ GASPS ]

128
00:08:34,891 --> 00:08:36,358
-WELL, WELL...

129
00:08:36,358 --> 00:08:38,025
THAT PERSON WRITING AT THAT DESK

130
00:08:38,025 --> 00:08:40,158
LOOKS A LOT LIKE ME
WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.

131
00:08:40,158 --> 00:08:42,491
COULD IT BE?
NO, I'M MISTAKEN.

132
00:08:42,491 --> 00:08:45,058
I WOULD NEVER WAVER
ABOUT WRITING.

133
00:08:45,058 --> 00:08:46,358
[ LAUGHS ]

134
00:08:47,625 --> 00:08:49,491
-SO, YOU'RE DROSSELMEYER.

135
00:08:49,491 --> 00:08:52,491
-HMM. THESE THINGS ALL LOOK
A LOT LIKE WHAT I USED,

136
00:08:52,491 --> 00:08:55,491
BUT MOST OF THEM
APPEAR TO BE FAKES.

137
00:08:55,491 --> 00:09:00,091
YOU'RE TRYING TO BE RESPONSIBLE
ABOUT YOUR WRITING, AREN'T YOU?

138
00:09:00,091 --> 00:09:02,191
WELL, THAT'S WHY
YOU CAN'T WRITE.

139
00:09:02,191 --> 00:09:05,458
YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND THAT
WHEN YOU'RE WRITING STORIES,

140
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:08,091
YOU SHOULD DO IT MORE FREELY
AND IRRESPONSIBLY.

141
00:09:08,091 --> 00:09:09,725
JUST FOLLOW YOUR OWN FEELINGS.

142
00:09:09,725 --> 00:09:11,991
-I HAVE NO DESIRE TO BECOME
LIKE YOU --

143
00:09:11,991 --> 00:09:13,491
A DEMENTED, SADISTIC FOSSIL

144
00:09:13,491 --> 00:09:15,791
WHO TOYS WITH PEOPLE'S FATES
FOR A LARK.

145
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:18,625
-THAT THINKING
WON'T GET US ANYWHERE.

146
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:19,858
-[ GASPS ]

147
00:09:19,858 --> 00:09:20,858
MYTHO.

148
00:09:20,858 --> 00:09:22,491
-THE RAVEN HAS REVIVED,

149
00:09:22,491 --> 00:09:25,225
AND ALL OF THE PRINCE'S HEART
IS RETURNED TO HIM,

150
00:09:25,225 --> 00:09:27,891
EXCEPT FOR THE SHARD
IN PRINCESS TUTU'S PENDANT.

151
00:09:27,891 --> 00:09:29,125
-WHAT?

152
00:09:29,125 --> 00:09:31,791
-BUT PRINCESS TUTU
CAN'T GIVE BACK THE PENDANT.

153
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:34,158
SO RIGHT NOW SHE'S SUFFERING.

154
00:09:34,158 --> 00:09:35,291
-[ GRUNTS ]

155
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:37,425
WHAT?
MY HAND'S WRITING BY ITSELF.

156
00:09:37,425 --> 00:09:39,158
-[ LAUGHS ]

157
00:09:39,158 --> 00:09:42,858
YOU SEE, YOU HAVE MY BLOOD
RUNNING THROUGH YOUR VEINS.

158
00:09:42,858 --> 00:09:43,891
-[ GRUNTS ]

159
00:09:43,891 --> 00:09:46,391
-THAT WAS THE LAKE
CALLED DESPAIR.

160
00:09:46,391 --> 00:09:49,625
IT WAS DARK AND DEEP,
JUST LIKE A DUCK'S EYES.

161
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:51,725
-WHAT ARE YOU INTENDING
TO MAKE ME WRITE?

162
00:09:51,725 --> 00:09:54,925
-THE SORROWFUL, YET BEAUTIFUL
STORY OF LITTLE DUCK.

163
00:09:54,925 --> 00:09:56,458
-THE STORY OF DUCK?

164
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:59,458
-AT THAT MOMENT,
DUCK COULD HEAR A VOICE.

165
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:01,991
IT WAS THE VOICE
OF DROSSELMEYER,

166
00:10:01,991 --> 00:10:04,191
THE MAN
WHO CONTROLLED THE STORY.

167
00:10:04,191 --> 00:10:05,591
-DUCK!

168
00:10:05,591 --> 00:10:08,391
-IT'S BECAUSE YOU'RE SCARED
TO LET GO OF BEING PRINCESS TUTU

169
00:10:08,391 --> 00:10:10,958
THAT YOU CAN'T GIVE BACK
THE HEART SHARD, RIGHT?

170
00:10:10,958 --> 00:10:12,225
-NO! THAT'S NOT IT!

171
00:10:12,225 --> 00:10:14,825
-YOU'RE AFRAID
TO PART WITH THE PRINCE.

172
00:10:14,825 --> 00:10:16,191
-I JUST WANT --

173
00:10:16,191 --> 00:10:19,291
-RUE WOULD BE CARVED INTO
THE PRINCE'S HEART FOR ETERNITY

174
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:22,491
BECAUSE SHE GAVE HERSELF OVER
TO THE RAVEN.

175
00:10:22,491 --> 00:10:24,725
AND BY KEEPING THE HEART SHARD,

176
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:27,725
DUCK WOULD LIVE ON
IN THE PRINCE'S HEART

177
00:10:27,725 --> 00:10:31,725
AS PRINCESS TUTU AND
NOT AS AN UGLY, LITTLE DUCK.

178
00:10:31,725 --> 00:10:34,725
-IS IT...
IS IT ALL MY FAULT?

179
00:10:34,725 --> 00:10:36,191
-YES, IT IS.

180
00:10:36,191 --> 00:10:38,691
AND IN ORDER
TO TAKE OFF THE PENDANT,

181
00:10:38,691 --> 00:10:40,925
YOU'LL HAVE TO LAY DOWN
YOUR LIFE.

182
00:10:40,925 --> 00:10:44,091
DUCK BEGAN TO SINK
INTO THE LAKE OF DESPAIR,

183
00:10:44,091 --> 00:10:46,358
WALKING FURTHER AND FURTHER IN.

184
00:10:46,358 --> 00:10:47,958
-STOP IT!

185
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,325
DON'T GO, DUCK!

186
00:10:49,325 --> 00:10:52,925
-DEEPER AND DEEPER.
-STOP IT!

187
00:10:57,191 --> 00:10:59,758
[ GROANING ]

188
00:10:59,758 --> 00:11:01,391
DUCK! [ GROANS ]

189
00:11:01,391 --> 00:11:02,625
[ THUMP! ]

190
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:05,491
-KIR!
THERE ARE CROWS ALL OVER TOWN!

191
00:11:05,491 --> 00:11:06,791
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

192
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,491
D-DUCK...

193
00:11:08,491 --> 00:11:11,191
-DUCK?
WHERE DID YOU GO, ZURA?

194
00:11:11,191 --> 00:11:12,591
DUCK!

195
00:11:12,591 --> 00:11:14,458
[ DRUMMING ]

196
00:11:31,801 --> 00:11:33,901
-I GOT TO FIND --
-DON'T GO OUT THERE!

197
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:35,301
IT'S DANGEROUS!
-WHAT?

198
00:11:35,301 --> 00:11:37,934
-NEVER MIND THAT.
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR HAND?

199
00:11:37,934 --> 00:11:40,068
AND WHEN DID YOU WRITE A STORY?

200
00:11:40,068 --> 00:11:41,768
WHAT HAPPENED?
TELL ME!

201
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:43,734
-DROSSELMEYER CAME, AND HE --
-DROSSELMEYER?

202
00:11:43,734 --> 00:11:45,634
-BASTARD MADE ME WRITE
THE STORY.

203
00:11:45,634 --> 00:11:48,701
-YOU MEAN DROSSELMEYER WAS HERE
IN THIS ROOM?

204
00:11:48,701 --> 00:11:50,968
-YES.
-MAGNIFICENT!

205
00:11:50,968 --> 00:11:55,034
[ GRUNTS ]
WHA-- WHAT'S WRONG?

206
00:11:55,034 --> 00:11:56,768
-NOTHING.

207
00:11:56,768 --> 00:12:00,268
-HEY, WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
HEY, WAIT!

208
00:12:00,268 --> 00:12:02,334
[ CAWING ]
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

209
00:12:02,334 --> 00:12:05,168
-IT -- IT LOOKS EXACTLY LIKE
THE CROW FESTIVAL SCENE

210
00:12:05,168 --> 00:12:07,701
THAT TOOK PLACE
IN "THE PRINCE AND THE RAVEN."

211
00:12:07,701 --> 00:12:09,201
[ CAWING CONTINUES ]

212
00:12:09,201 --> 00:12:11,768
-SO THE RAVEN HAS CURSED THEM.

213
00:12:11,768 --> 00:12:12,868
DAMN IT!
-HEY!

214
00:12:12,868 --> 00:12:15,101
THE RAVEN'S CURSE, IS IT?

215
00:12:15,101 --> 00:12:17,368
I WONDER
IF SHE'S ALL RIGHT, THEN.

216
00:12:17,368 --> 00:12:19,368
-[ Thinking ]
THE LAKE OF DESPAIR.

217
00:12:19,368 --> 00:12:21,868
WHERE IS THAT?

218
00:12:21,868 --> 00:12:23,834
-THERE YOU ARE, ZURA.

219
00:12:23,834 --> 00:12:26,634
-UZURA?
-DUCK JUST DISAPPEARED, ZURA.

220
00:12:26,634 --> 00:12:28,868
-SO, YOU WERE WITH HER
WHEN IT HAPPENED?

221
00:12:28,868 --> 00:12:31,668
WHERE IS SHE?
-THIS WAY, ZURA.

222
00:12:35,501 --> 00:12:37,668
-I'M SORRY.

223
00:12:37,668 --> 00:12:40,368
I'M SORRY, RUE.

224
00:12:40,368 --> 00:12:43,634
I'M SORRY, MYTHO.

225
00:12:43,634 --> 00:12:47,501
IF I VANISH...

226
00:12:47,501 --> 00:12:53,068
THE HEART SHARD
WILL RETURN TO YOU.

227
00:12:53,068 --> 00:12:55,901
[ DRUMMING ]
-THIS WAY, ZURA.

228
00:12:55,901 --> 00:12:59,134
-[ Thinking ] WHAT?
OUTSIDE THE GATE?

229
00:12:59,134 --> 00:13:03,168
I'VE NEVER EVEN THOUGHT
OF LEAVING THIS CITY.

230
00:13:03,168 --> 00:13:04,934
NOW I SEE.

231
00:13:04,934 --> 00:13:07,268
I WAS BEING CONTROLLED
BY DROSSELMEYER'S STORY.

232
00:13:07,268 --> 00:13:08,668
THAT'S WHY.

233
00:13:08,668 --> 00:13:13,334
LOOKS LIKE THE STORY STARTED
TO SPREAD BEYOND THE CITY WALLS.

234
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,834
-WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR, ZURA?

235
00:13:15,834 --> 00:13:16,868
-OH, SORRY.

236
00:13:16,868 --> 00:13:18,134
-HURRY UP, ZURA.

237
00:13:18,134 --> 00:13:20,434
-[ GRUNTS ]

238
00:13:25,168 --> 00:13:27,068
-HERE, ZURA.

239
00:13:27,068 --> 00:13:29,901
-DUCK?

240
00:13:32,034 --> 00:13:34,234
WHAT'S WITH THIS LAKE?

241
00:13:34,234 --> 00:13:36,568
FOR SOME REASON, I CAN BREATHE.

242
00:13:36,568 --> 00:13:40,268
IS THIS JUST ANOTHER STAGED
SETTING DROSSELMEYER PREPARED?

243
00:13:44,468 --> 00:13:49,034
-[ Thinking ] I THOUGHT I WAS
DOING MY BEST FOR MYTHO'S SAKE.

244
00:13:49,034 --> 00:13:52,701
BUT WAS IT FOR MY OWN SAKE?

245
00:13:52,701 --> 00:13:57,434
JUST LIKE MR. DROSSELMEYER SAID,
I'M REALLY THINKING

246
00:13:57,434 --> 00:14:00,268
THAT I DON'T WANT TO RETURN
MYTHO TO THE STORY.

247
00:14:03,568 --> 00:14:05,568
-DUCK.

248
00:14:05,568 --> 00:14:08,201
DUCK!

249
00:14:08,201 --> 00:14:09,901
DUCK!

250
00:14:09,901 --> 00:14:11,034
-FAKIR?

251
00:14:13,134 --> 00:14:15,468
FAKIR!

252
00:14:17,901 --> 00:14:18,968
-DUCK?

253
00:14:18,968 --> 00:14:21,401
-FAKIR,
THE PENDANT WON'T COME OFF.

254
00:14:22,701 --> 00:14:26,134
IT'S THE LAST
OF MYTHO'S HEART SHARDS.

255
00:14:26,134 --> 00:14:30,068
AND MYTHO ASKED ME
TO GIVE IT BACK TO HIM, BUT...

256
00:14:30,068 --> 00:14:33,168
MYTHO SAID HE WANTS TO MAKE RUE
HIS PRINCESS,

257
00:14:33,168 --> 00:14:36,234
AND I KNOW HE WANTS TO SAVE HER
FROM THE RAVEN.

258
00:14:36,234 --> 00:14:37,801
[ SOBS ]

259
00:14:37,801 --> 00:14:40,368
[ Voice breaking ]
BUT IT JUST WON'T COME OFF.

260
00:14:40,368 --> 00:14:42,334
ALL THIS IS MY FAULT.

261
00:14:42,334 --> 00:14:44,901
BECAUSE I'M THINKING
THAT DEEP INSIDE MY HEART,

262
00:14:44,901 --> 00:14:46,801
I DON'T WANT THE STORY
TO EVER END.

263
00:14:46,801 --> 00:14:51,434
PIKE AND LILIE AND MR. CAT AND
THE OTHERS TURNED INTO CROWS,

264
00:14:51,434 --> 00:14:53,601
BUT EVEN AFTER THAT...

265
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:54,968
[ CRYING ]

266
00:14:54,968 --> 00:14:57,468
-IDIOT.
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE.

267
00:14:57,468 --> 00:15:00,134
-WHAT?
-YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE, DUCK.

268
00:15:00,134 --> 00:15:01,201
I DON'T WANT TO --

269
00:15:01,201 --> 00:15:02,601
NO, THE FACT OF THE MATTER

270
00:15:02,601 --> 00:15:05,534
IS THAT NOBODY WANTS TO SEE
THE STORY COME TO AN END --

271
00:15:05,534 --> 00:15:08,734
NOBODY, SAVE MYTHO HIMSELF.

272
00:15:08,734 --> 00:15:12,001
I STILL CAN'T WRITE A STORY
ABOUT MYTHO, EITHER.

273
00:15:17,834 --> 00:15:20,634
STOP BLAMING JUST YOURSELF.

274
00:15:20,634 --> 00:15:24,601
EVERYONE IS SCARED OF BEING
RESTORED TO THEIR TRUE SELVES.

275
00:15:24,601 --> 00:15:27,734
THEY'RE USED TO BEING GIVEN
ROLES IN STORIES

276
00:15:27,734 --> 00:15:30,268
THAT SHELTER THEM
FROM THE BUSINESS OF LIVING.

277
00:15:31,234 --> 00:15:33,401
THE REAL YOU...

278
00:15:33,401 --> 00:15:35,434
IS A DUCK.

279
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:38,334
AND THE REAL ME...

280
00:15:38,334 --> 00:15:42,134
IN THE END, THE REAL ME HAS BEEN
PROTECTED SINCE MY CHILDHOOD.

281
00:15:42,134 --> 00:15:44,134
-HUH?

282
00:15:44,134 --> 00:15:47,634
-I CAN'T PROTECT ANYONE.

283
00:15:47,634 --> 00:15:50,368
BUT EVEN IF THAT
IS WHAT I AM TRULY LIKE,

284
00:15:50,368 --> 00:15:53,101
I WANT TO END THE STORY
ONCE AND FOR ALL.

285
00:15:53,101 --> 00:15:56,801
I WANT TO PROTECT MYTHO AND YOU
BECAUSE OF MY OWN FEELINGS,

286
00:15:56,801 --> 00:16:01,401
NOT SOME ROLE GIVEN TO ME, EVEN
IF I USE UP ALL OF MY POWER.

287
00:16:01,401 --> 00:16:04,668
-WHEN THAT HAPPENS, I'LL GO BACK
TO BEING JUST A BIRD.

288
00:16:04,668 --> 00:16:07,634
AND I WON'T EVER STUDY BALLET
WITH EVERYBODY AGAIN.

289
00:16:07,634 --> 00:16:09,134
-THAT'S FINE, ISN'T IT?

290
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:11,601
AFTER ALL,
THAT'S WHO YOU REALLY ARE.

291
00:16:11,601 --> 00:16:12,601
-YEAH.

292
00:16:12,601 --> 00:16:14,534
-AND EVEN AFTER THAT TIME COMES,

293
00:16:14,534 --> 00:16:16,701
I WILL STAY BY YOUR SIDE
FOREVER.

294
00:16:16,701 --> 00:16:18,501
-[ Voice breaking ] FAKIR.

295
00:16:19,534 --> 00:16:21,434
[ Thinking ] IT'S STRANGE.

296
00:16:21,434 --> 00:16:23,234
UNTIL A SHORT WHILE AGO,

297
00:16:23,234 --> 00:16:28,101
I THOUGHT IT WAS OKAY FOR ME TO
SIMPLY VANISH, BUT NOW I'M WEAK.

298
00:16:28,101 --> 00:16:32,834
BUT FOR SOME REASON, FAKIR
ALWAYS MAKES ME STRONGER...

299
00:16:32,834 --> 00:16:34,368
SOMEHOW.

300
00:16:36,701 --> 00:16:39,868
-LET'S GO BACK TO BEING
OUR TRUE SELVES NOW.

301
00:16:39,868 --> 00:16:40,968
-YES.

302
00:16:40,968 --> 00:16:43,068
-LET'S COMPOSE AN END
FOR THIS STORY,

303
00:16:43,068 --> 00:16:47,368
NOT JUST FOR MYTHO'S SAKE,
BUT FOR OUR OWN SAKES, AS WELL.

304
00:16:47,368 --> 00:16:48,401
-YES.

305
00:16:48,401 --> 00:16:49,434
[ TING! ]

306
00:16:49,434 --> 00:16:50,901
[ CLASP CLICKS ]

307
00:16:50,901 --> 00:16:52,501
[ GASPS ]

308
00:16:52,501 --> 00:16:54,534
IT CAME OFF.

309
00:16:54,534 --> 00:16:58,501
HEY, THE PENDANT CAME OFF
JUST NOW, FAKIR.

310
00:16:58,501 --> 00:17:01,301
-LET'S RETURN IT TO MYTHO.

311
00:17:01,301 --> 00:17:02,251
[ RUMBLING ]
-AAH!

312
00:17:06,012 --> 00:17:08,745
WHOA! AAAAAH!

313
00:17:08,745 --> 00:17:10,412
-[ CHUCKLES EVILLY ]

314
00:17:10,412 --> 00:17:14,812
THE SPELL
RUNS MUCH DEEPER THAN THAT.

315
00:17:19,345 --> 00:17:21,412
-IT'S RUE.

316
00:17:27,245 --> 00:17:28,878
RUE, I'M COMING TO GET YOU!

317
00:17:28,878 --> 00:17:30,212
-HOLD ON.
-HUH?

318
00:17:31,745 --> 00:17:34,312
LET'S GO BACK.
-WHAT ABOUT RUE?

319
00:17:34,312 --> 00:17:38,012
-MYTHO WILL BE ABLE TO SAVE RUE.
OUR JOB IS TO SAVE MYTHO.

320
00:17:38,012 --> 00:17:40,012
WE HAVE TO HURRY.

321
00:17:40,012 --> 00:17:41,578
-RIGHT.

322
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,845
-THAT'S UZURA.
SHE'LL GUIDE US OUT OF HERE.

323
00:17:45,845 --> 00:17:47,645
[ DISTANT DRUMMING ]

324
00:17:53,645 --> 00:17:57,045
-HUH?

325
00:17:57,045 --> 00:18:00,612
OH, ARE YOU OKAY, ZURA?

326
00:18:00,612 --> 00:18:03,678
-THANK YOU SO MUCH, UZURA.
-YES, THANK YOU.

327
00:18:03,678 --> 00:18:05,778
-YOU TOOK YOUR PENDANT OFF,
ZURA.

328
00:18:05,778 --> 00:18:08,612
-UH-HUH. WE GOT TO GIVE IT BACK
TO MYTHO FAST.

329
00:18:08,612 --> 00:18:10,612
-OH.
-FAKIR...

330
00:18:10,612 --> 00:18:13,912
WILL YOU WRITE A STORY ABOUT ME
JUST ONE MORE TIME?

331
00:18:13,912 --> 00:18:15,245
-HUH?
-THAT WAY,

332
00:18:15,245 --> 00:18:17,978
WE'LL COMBINE OUR "WE
WANT TO PROTECT MYTHO" POWERS.

333
00:18:17,978 --> 00:18:21,345
-COMBINE OUR POWERS, HUH?
-MM.

334
00:18:24,712 --> 00:18:28,212
-IS IT REALLY OKAY FOR ME
TO WRITE A STORY ABOUT YOU?

335
00:18:28,212 --> 00:18:29,212
-YEAH.

336
00:18:29,212 --> 00:18:31,278
OKAY, THEN.
I'LL BE BACK.

337
00:18:31,278 --> 00:18:32,478
-RIGHT.

338
00:18:32,478 --> 00:18:34,412
-WELL, GOODBYE, UZURA.

339
00:18:35,678 --> 00:18:36,945
ALL RIGHT.

340
00:18:36,945 --> 00:18:38,412
OH.

341
00:18:38,412 --> 00:18:40,912
HUH?

342
00:18:40,912 --> 00:18:42,645
UZURA...

343
00:18:46,445 --> 00:18:49,945
-PRINCESS TUTU, HUH?

344
00:18:49,945 --> 00:18:51,845
[ DRUMMING ]

345
00:18:51,845 --> 00:18:52,912
-HUH?

346
00:18:54,345 --> 00:18:57,878
-HEY, DUCK!
DO YOUR BEST, ZURA!

347
00:19:01,678 --> 00:19:03,645
-[ Thinking ] PRINCESS TUTU RAN,

348
00:19:03,645 --> 00:19:07,845
DETERMINED TO RETURN THE LAST
HEART SHARD TO THE PRINCE.

349
00:19:07,845 --> 00:19:12,778
SHE DIDN'T DO IT JUST FOR THE
PRINCE, BUT FOR ALL THE PEOPLE.

350
00:19:12,778 --> 00:19:15,778
WHEN SHE THOUGHT OF IT THAT WAY,
THERE WAS NO MORE HESITATION.

351
00:19:15,778 --> 00:19:17,812
[ TWINKLE! ]

352
00:19:25,112 --> 00:19:27,612
[ TWINKLE! ]

353
00:19:30,045 --> 00:19:34,212
THE MORNING BELL
HAD NOT YET RUNG.

354
00:19:34,212 --> 00:19:37,912
THE PRINCE WAS QUIETLY WAITING
FOR TUTU TO COME.

355
00:19:45,278 --> 00:19:47,545
-PRINCE, I'M SORRY
TO HAVE MADE YOU WAIT.

356
00:19:47,545 --> 00:19:50,445
-I NEVER DOUBTED
YOU WOULD COME FOR ME.

357
00:19:50,445 --> 00:19:52,678
-[ GASPS LIGHTLY ]
-THE FEELINGS

358
00:19:52,678 --> 00:19:53,978
YOU RETURN TO ME --

359
00:19:53,978 --> 00:19:58,745
THE FEELINGS OF LOVE,
AFFECTION, SORROW, LONELINESS --

360
00:19:58,745 --> 00:20:03,112
ALL OF MY FEELINGS TOLD ME THAT
TUTU WAS SURE TO COME FOR ME.

361
00:20:07,145 --> 00:20:09,745
[ TWINKLE! ]

362
00:20:13,678 --> 00:20:17,112
-TUTU QUIETLY GAZED
INTO THE PRINCE'S EYES

363
00:20:17,112 --> 00:20:19,945
THEN TOOK OFF THE PENDANT.

364
00:20:19,945 --> 00:20:21,545
THE FINAL HEART SHARD

365
00:20:21,545 --> 00:20:25,378
WAS SHAPED LIKE
A PAIR OF FLUTTERING WINGS --

366
00:20:25,378 --> 00:20:27,845
WINGS FOR THE PEOPLE
WHO HAD SPENT A COMFORTABLE TIME

367
00:20:27,845 --> 00:20:33,078
INSIDE THE STORY
TO LEAVE THE NEST WITH.

368
00:20:33,078 --> 00:20:36,012
-WINGS FOR THE PRINCE
TO RETURN TO HIMSELF WITH.

369
00:20:36,012 --> 00:20:38,412
[ TWINKLE! ]

370
00:20:44,778 --> 00:20:46,045
-[ CHUCKLES ]

371
00:20:47,478 --> 00:20:49,812
-GOODBYE NOW, MYTHO.
[ TWINKLE! ]

372
00:20:49,812 --> 00:20:52,078
GOODBYE.

373
00:20:52,078 --> 00:20:54,078
-TUTU...

374
00:20:54,078 --> 00:20:56,045
-QUACK!

375
00:20:58,445 --> 00:21:01,478
-YOU WERE...
-QUACK.

376
00:21:01,478 --> 00:21:05,045
-SOMETHING SO SMALL AND FRAGILE
ACCOMPLISHED THIS.

377
00:21:08,212 --> 00:21:10,912
THANK YOU, PRINCESS TUTU.

378
00:21:10,912 --> 00:21:12,512
-QUACK?

379
00:21:18,878 --> 00:21:22,145
-THIS IS THE TRUE PRINCE.

380
00:21:22,145 --> 00:21:24,145
[ BELL TOLLING ]
-[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

381
00:21:24,145 --> 00:21:28,545
SO, YOU'VE FINALLY BEEN
RESTORED, PRINCE.

382
00:21:28,545 --> 00:21:30,312
[ TWINKLE! ]

383
00:21:39,845 --> 00:21:40,845
HMM?

384
00:21:40,845 --> 00:21:44,112
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

385
00:21:44,112 --> 00:21:46,345
-IT'S THE BEGINNING
OF A TRAGEDY.

386
00:21:46,345 --> 00:21:49,045
THE PRINCE CAN'T FIGHT
FOR HIS PRINCESS' CAPTURE

387
00:21:49,045 --> 00:21:50,212
INSIDE THE ENEMY.

388
00:21:50,212 --> 00:21:51,945
TUTU HAS BECOME A MERE DUCK,

389
00:21:51,945 --> 00:21:54,145
THE KNIGHT
HAS LONG BEEN USELESS,

390
00:21:54,145 --> 00:21:57,678
AND THE PRINCESS WILL WASTE AWAY
IN THE DEPTHS OF DESPAIR.

391
00:21:57,678 --> 00:21:59,878
WHAT WILL YOU DO NOW, PRINCE?

392
00:21:59,878 --> 00:22:03,145
WILL YOU SHATTER YOUR HEART
A SECOND TIME?

393
00:22:03,145 --> 00:22:04,745
[ CHUCKLES EVILLY ]

394
00:22:17,612 --> 00:22:19,645
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

395
00:22:49,612 --> 00:22:51,645
[ SINGING IN JAPANESE
CONTINUES ]

396
00:23:34,712 --> 00:23:40,345
-THE REAL ME IS JUST A DUCK,
BUT I CAN STILL DANCE.

397
00:23:40,345 --> 00:23:43,445
-NO ONE TO TRICK ME,
NO ONE FOR ME TO RESENT.

398
00:23:43,445 --> 00:23:47,012
THERE'S NOTHING HERE,
NOT EVEN LOVING.

399
00:23:47,012 --> 00:23:49,178
-EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED
IN GOLD CROWN TOWN

400
00:23:49,178 --> 00:23:50,912
THIS THING WAS RECORDING
AS A STORY.

401
00:23:50,912 --> 00:23:54,712
-IN MY NAME AS PRINCE SIEGFRIED,
I CALL THE NAME OF THE PRINCESS!

402
00:23:54,712 --> 00:23:57,712
-LET'S GIVE THIS STORY
A HAPPY ENDING.

403
00:23:57,712 --> 00:24:02,878
-ALL YOU CHILDREN WHO LOVE
STORIES, COME, GATHER 'ROUND.

404
00:24:02,878 --> 00:24:04,578
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

